A vintage-style illustration depicting a craftsman's wooden workbench scattered with geometric wooden shapes — cubes, cylinders, pyramids, and spheres — alongside a worn wooden board with various differently-shaped holes cut into it. Some shapes are wedged awkwardly into mismatched holes, others sit waiting. Warm afternoon light streams through a dusty workshop window, casting long shadows across the weathered wood grain. In the background, barely visible, hangs an old Chinese scroll with abstract brushwork patterns. The color palette features rich amber, deep walnut browns, and soft cream tones, evoking 1940s technical illustrations with crosshatching and subtle texture. Tools like calipers and a small chisel rest nearby, suggesting careful measurement and the challenge of fitting disparate things together.
